Greenko Climbs in London After Directors Acquire Stake From Private Equity

-- B y   T o d d   W h i t e
-- 
2011-03-07T09:11:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/greenko-climbs-in-london-after-directors-acquire-stake-from-private-equity.html
  Greenko Group Plc (GKO)  rose as much as 11
percent in  London  after Executive Directors Mahesh Kolli and
Anil Chalamalasetty bought a stake in the alternative-energy
company from Aloe Private Equity at an above-market price.  The stock rose as high as 215 pence and traded at 208 pence
as of 8:27 a.m. local time.   The Isle of Man, U.K.-based company said today in a filing
that the directors bought 4.5 million shares through their
jointly owned ACMK Enterprise Ltd. at 225 pence each, with 2.25
million pounds ($3.67 million) having been paid at the time of
the transaction and the balance owed before February 2013.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Todd White at 
 twhite2@bloomberg.net  